Body: I've just found out about Google Location history and it correctly displays all the places I've been to in Bolivia to-a-T. Really accurate.What concerns me is that there is a dot in Singapore! I've never been anywhere near that country. Not even 2000 miles near.My question is, if someone logged into my account from that country, would that dot load from there? Should I change my passwords ASAP?
Title: Google Location history showing me in another continent? Did someone hack me?

history.Text: I've just found out about Google Location history and it correctly displays all the places I've been to in Bolivia to-a-T. Really accurate.What concerns me is that there is a dot in Beking, Singapore! I've never been anywhere near that country. Not even 2000 miles near.![enter image description here][1]My question is, if someone logged into my account from that country, would that dot load from there? Should I change my passwords ASAP?Thanks  [1]: http://i.stack.imgur.com/Pwdjk.png
